Although other [[Slayer master]] [[Slayer task|tasks]] may be completed in both [[Wilderness]] and mainland locations, all of [[Krystilia]]'s tasks must be done in the Wilderness. That means players should only take [[gear]] they are willing to lose.

'''{{colour|red|Warning}}:''' Assess and mitigate [[risks]], and do '''not''' ever take any items you cannot afford to lose!

==Map of the Wilderness==
[[File:Wilderness map.png|700px]]

==Requirements==
[[Krystilia]] has no requirements, but players should be sufficient enough to survive in the [[Wilderness]]. They should also possess decent [[stats]] since she can assign [[monsters]] ranging from [[Combat level]] 8 to 470, especially in terms of [[Wilderness bosses]].

===Suggested skills===
*{{SCP|Attack|60+}}
*{{SCP|Strength|60+}}
*{{SCP|Defence|40+}}
*{{SCP|Ranged|61+}}
*{{SCP|Prayer|43+}} ([[Protect from Melee]] and all [[protection prayers]])
*{{SCP|Magic|35+}} ([[Fire Bolt]] or a better [[spell]] recommended if using)

==== Agility ====
High [[Agility]] is an advantage in the [[Wilderness]]. The energy restoration rate is useful, since you often need to travel longer distances on foot in the Wilderness. Furthermore, [[run energy]] may be important when fleeing [[player killers]]. Additionally, access to the following [[shortcuts]] may make both travel and fleeing easier:

* {{SCP|Agility|46}} (crevice in [[Deep Wilderness Dungeon]], requires completion of [[Medium Wilderness Diary]])
* {{SCP|Agility|60}} (no-exit climb close to the [[God Wars Dungeon]] entrance)
* {{SCP|Agility|64}} (no-exit climb from [[Trollheim]])
* {{SCP|Agility|65}} (easy [[Revenant Caves]] jump)
* {{SCP|Agility|74}} ([[Lava Dragon Isle]] jump, requires completion of [[Hard Wilderness Diary]])
* {{SCP|Agility|75}} (medium Revenant Caves jump)
* {{SCP|Agility|82}} ([[Lava Maze]] jump, requires completion of Hard Wilderness Diary)
* {{SCP|Agility|89}} (hard Revenant Caves jump)

==Equipment==
As you are in the [[Wilderness]], the last thing you want to do is [[Skull (status)|skull]], so set [[player options]] to hidden. Skulling in the Wilderness means you are limited to keeping only one item in [[Items Kept on Death]] only if [[Protect Item]] is activated and not deactivated by [[Smite]]. If you die while skulled while Protect Item was deactivated or [[smited]], you '''will''' lose all items.

'''Note:''' Also, [[Accept Aid]] should be set to off. There is no reason to have it on otherwise.

